      • getNestedFieldValue

        public static java.lang.Object getNestedFieldValue​(java.lang.String nestedPropertyPath,
                                                   java.lang.Object rootInstance)
        Retrieves a field value described by a nested path (nestedPropertyPath.

        In case the nestedPathProperty resolves to an instance of type Property, the property value and not the property itself is returned (because we do not do direct field access, but we use the corresponding getter-method. Getter-methods on properties return the value, not the property).

        In case you need access to the Property instance itself, please use method getNestedFieldProperty(String, Object), which uses the property-getter and not the regular getter for retrieving the field instance.

        In case one of the path elements of the nested path evaluates to null, null is returned by this method.

        Parameters:
        nestedPropertyPath - a nested path to a property
        rootInstance - the instance that the nested property path is referring to
        Returns:
        the instance that is the provider of the filed

      • getNestedFieldProperty

        public static <T> javafx.beans.value.ObservableValue<T> getNestedFieldProperty​(java.lang.String nestedPropertyPath,
                                                                               java.lang.Object rootInstance)
        Retrieves a field value described by a nested path (nestedPropertyPath. The value is expected to be of type ObservableValue.

        Unlike method getNestedFieldValue(String, Object), this method uses the "property-getter" method for accessing the property (which is "propertyNameProperty()" for a property with name "propertyName").

        In case one of the path elements of the nested path evaluates to null, null is returned by this method.

        Parameters:
        nestedPropertyPath - a nested path to a property
        rootInstance - the instance that the nested property path is referring to
        Returns:
        the instance that is the provider of the property

      • getFieldValueByPropertyGetter

        public static java.lang.Object getFieldValueByPropertyGetter​(java.lang.reflect.Field field,
                                                             java.lang.Object instance)
        Gets the value from the supplied Field and instance, but by trying to access the corresponding property-getter method. This method is sometimes to be preferred over the direct field access, especially when a lazy-initialization of the field is performed in the respective getter method.

        The name of the property-getter for a field with name "field" is derived as fieldProperty().

        Parameters:
        field - the field
        instance - the instance holding the value for the field
        Returns:
        the field value
